Java loop

definition: loop is repeating set of statement(s) executed while a certain conditon remains
	true
	
uses of loops:	
				reading from a file until end of file (eof)
				get data from user at prompt
				validation loop
				look up values in an array (table)
			
			
pre test:

	//use for file processing, user entry loop, validate data entry
	
	while(condition ){
		//loop body
	}

	//use for a predefined number of iterations, processing arrays
	for (int i = 0; i<10; i++){
		//loop body
	}

post test:

	//use for user entry

	do{
	//loop body
	}while(condition);
	
	
